{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_52","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve narrowed the remaining issue further: log4j’s `PluginBuilder` reflects not just over `OpenTelemetryAppender` itself, but over the appender builder class hierarchy to read `@PluginBuilderAttribute` fields like `name`, `layout`, `filter`, and the OpenTelemetry-specific options. If those declared fields aren’t registered, log4j can quietly fail plugin construction and leave the XML appender absent. I’m checking that builder hierarchy now so I can add the smallest field/method registrations that cover the XML path."}}
